Columns: 1 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 35;
                                                  written lines: 35; Uniform layout. Visible pricking and ruling with a plummet (each bifolium on both sides). Hair-side and flesh-side of the folios indistinguishable. Fine parchment.Last line written within the ruling.Arranged in two columns between folios 322r-353r.Catchwords at the end of quires.Initial words written in large characters.Occasional infralinear vocalization.Maniculae on folios 87v, 88r, 281r. 
										Watermark, folio 355, of a crown with a horn, similar to 5073 (dated 1569-1570 to Remiremont).
